WEBVTT

00:01.871 --> 00:03.220
Previously onThis Is Us...

00:03.264 --> 00:04.482
OFFICIANT:
You may now kiss the bride.

00:05.788 --> 00:07.050
BETH:
"I would never

00:07.094 --> 00:10.053
leave you lost."
In female handwriting.

00:10.097 --> 00:11.881
This a love letter?

00:11.924 --> 00:13.926
Look, a bra.

00:13.970 --> 00:15.841
BETH:
And it's right next to some kind
of floral wrap thingy.

00:15.885 --> 00:18.540
Who do you think
he slept with last night?

00:19.802 --> 00:22.979
MADISON: It could be the
wedding singer. Philip's friend.

00:23.023 --> 00:24.459
-She was
at the rehearsal last night.
-Mm-hmm.

00:24.502 --> 00:26.939
And they were talking.

00:26.983 --> 00:29.072
-[Randall speaking indistinctly]
-MADISON: [gasps] Wait.

00:29.116 --> 00:31.727
Did you see that look
Sophie just gave him?

00:31.770 --> 00:34.121
-They have
crazy history together.
-Mm-hmm.

00:34.164 --> 00:35.905
MADISON:
But wait. She's married.

00:35.948 --> 00:38.429
-Oh, yeah. That's not her MO.
-Mm. No.

00:38.473 --> 00:40.997
-BETH: Then there's Cassidy,
his plus-one.
-MADISON: Right.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.520
Just as a friend, though.

00:42.564 --> 00:44.261
RANDALL:
So, for real, bro,

00:44.305 --> 00:46.437
what happened
with you last night?

00:46.481 --> 00:49.005
Oh, man, it's a long story.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.354
Is it a good story?

00:51.747 --> 00:53.183
[exhales]

00:55.011 --> 00:57.144
♪

01:26.434 --> 01:31.134
-ARIELLE: ♪ Wise men say...♪
-[indistinct chatter]

01:33.441 --> 01:36.313
What time it is.
You guys have the time?

01:36.357 --> 01:38.141
Uh, we're about to have
our rehearsal dinner.

01:38.185 --> 01:40.752
-Do you have somewhere else
to be? I don't...
-KEVIN: No.

01:40.796 --> 01:43.842
No, that's not what I was...
talking about at all.

01:43.886 --> 01:45.148
KATE:
Mm-hmm.

01:45.192 --> 01:48.151
She's really something, huh?

01:48.195 --> 01:50.806
-♪ Falling in love...♪
-[Kate sighs]

01:50.849 --> 01:52.547
Pearson kryptonite.
Hot singers onstage

01:52.590 --> 01:54.157
singing rock classics.

01:54.201 --> 01:57.334
-It's how Dad fell for Mom.
-Yeah.

01:57.378 --> 02:00.294
Oh, uh, "Moonshadow," right?

02:00.337 --> 02:01.599
-Wow.
-KATE: Mm-hmm.

02:01.643 --> 02:03.297
I had to brush up
on my Pearson trivia

02:03.340 --> 02:06.169
before, you know, marrying one.

02:06.213 --> 02:07.953
-KATE: Mm.
-Aw.

02:07.997 --> 02:10.217
-[Philip chuckles]
-KATE: Let's go say hi
to somebody else.

02:10.260 --> 02:11.392
-All right, have fun.
-KATE: Okay.

02:14.003 --> 02:18.834
♪ So, take my hand...♪

02:18.877 --> 02:21.228
-Looking good, Pearson.
-Oh, thank you very, very much.

02:21.271 --> 02:23.012
You're not looking so bad
yourself.

02:23.055 --> 02:24.666
I'm wearing makeup.
I can't wait to wash my face.

02:24.709 --> 02:26.233
But also, yeah, I know.

02:26.276 --> 02:28.409
-You know. [laughs]
-I do.

02:28.452 --> 02:30.237
♪ But I...♪

02:30.280 --> 02:33.240
-Manny say "slut." [laughs]
-Well, hey.

02:33.283 --> 02:35.242
Haven't heard that one before.
Hi.

02:35.285 --> 02:38.070
-Oliver. Philip's cousin.
-Kevin.

02:38.114 --> 02:41.117
Oh. So, I, uh, hear you and I

02:41.161 --> 02:43.598
are the only eligible blokes
at this shindig.

02:43.641 --> 02:46.209
Any thoughts
on who you want to go for?

02:46.253 --> 02:48.298
I-I don't want
to step on any toes

02:48.342 --> 02:49.691
or cross any swords.

02:49.734 --> 02:51.388
U-Unless you're into that.

02:51.432 --> 02:53.434
No. I... You know, I was...
I was actually just here

02:53.477 --> 02:55.349
to celebrate
with Kate and Philip, so...

02:55.392 --> 02:57.089
Okay.

02:57.133 --> 02:58.221
[chuckles]

02:58.265 --> 03:00.441
Okay. Easy. Easy.

03:00.484 --> 03:03.226
Yeah, you got it. Pace yourself.

03:04.271 --> 03:06.751
-Oliver. Yeah.
-RANDALL: Hmm.

03:07.709 --> 03:08.927
What?

03:08.971 --> 03:10.451
Come on, man.

03:10.494 --> 03:12.235
We both know you've been staring

03:12.279 --> 03:15.412
at that door, willing Sophie
to walk through it all day.

03:15.456 --> 03:17.153
No, I don't even know
what you're talking about.

03:17.197 --> 03:18.720
-I have not been doing
any of those things.
-RANDALL: Mm-hmm.

03:18.763 --> 03:21.157
How many times have you seen her
in the last few years?

03:21.201 --> 03:23.464
Just twice. You know, I saw her
once at her mother's funeral,

03:23.507 --> 03:27.250
and then I saw her again at Kate
and Philip's engagement party.

03:27.294 --> 03:29.252
She's a married woman, Kev.

03:29.296 --> 03:32.342
Don't cause any drama
at our sister's wedding.

03:32.386 --> 03:35.171
Look, Sophie and I are cool.
All right, man?

03:35.215 --> 03:37.217
We're...

03:41.525 --> 03:43.266
Nothing to worry about.

03:45.921 --> 03:47.270
RANDALL:
Right.

03:47.314 --> 03:51.448
♪ Can't help♪

03:51.492 --> 03:55.452
♪ Falling in love♪

03:55.496 --> 04:01.458
♪ With you.♪

04:01.502 --> 04:03.286
REBECCA:
Sophie, it's so good to see you.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.288
You must be so tired.

04:05.332 --> 04:07.899
Oh, my gosh, I must look it.
I just had

04:07.943 --> 04:10.989
-a really,
really long plane ride.
-How's college?

04:11.033 --> 04:12.121
How are you and Kevin

04:12.164 --> 04:14.515
handling the long distance?

04:14.558 --> 04:17.735
Oh. Um... It's,

04:17.779 --> 04:20.303
-uh...
-REBECCA: Yeah,
I-I know it's rough,

04:20.347 --> 04:21.696
but hang in there.

04:21.739 --> 04:23.480
Yeah.

04:23.524 --> 04:25.700
Well, it's-it's really wonderful
to see you again.

04:25.743 --> 04:27.310
REBECCA:
Mm. It's good to see you,

04:27.354 --> 04:29.399
-too.
-SOPHIE: Yeah.

04:31.140 --> 04:32.924
[Sophie chuckles softly]

04:32.968 --> 04:34.317
-Hey.
-Hey.

04:34.361 --> 04:35.971
I'm just so sorry
about all this,

04:36.014 --> 04:37.320
um, but I'm Arielle,

04:37.364 --> 04:38.887
and I'm gonna give you
a big hug right now.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.106
-Oh. Yeah, okay.
-Okay.

04:41.150 --> 04:43.065
Can you see the man behind me?

04:44.371 --> 04:46.503
Oh, yeah.
That's, uh, that's Oliver.

04:46.547 --> 04:49.332
-Is he still there?
-He is still there.

04:49.376 --> 04:50.377
-I'm so sorry.
-Yeah.

04:50.420 --> 04:52.379
I-I've just been meaning
to tell you,

04:52.422 --> 04:55.033
I am your biggest fan!

04:55.077 --> 04:57.166
I mean, that season finale?

04:57.209 --> 04:59.560
I mean, I didn't know

04:59.603 --> 05:01.562
-a sitcom could be
so heartwarming!
-KEVIN: Well,

05:01.605 --> 05:03.303
-thank you very,
very much. Um...
-[chuckles] Yeah.

05:04.652 --> 05:06.349
Hugh Grant's opposite
has-has left. I think

05:06.393 --> 05:08.395
-the coast is clear.
-[sighs] Thank you.

05:08.438 --> 05:10.048
Yeah, no problem.
Anything for a fan.

05:10.092 --> 05:11.354
Oh.

05:11.398 --> 05:14.488
Actually,
I've never seen your show.

05:14.531 --> 05:17.360
-Yeah. Yeah.
-[chuckles] I'm just more
of a podcast person.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.840
No, honestly, I couldn't be
less offended, really.

05:18.883 --> 05:20.929
That's, uh... It's... You know,

05:20.972 --> 05:23.061
I'm-I'm gonna go talk
to an old friend real quick.

05:23.105 --> 05:25.412
-Of course. Mm-hmm.
-Okay? It was good
talking to you.

05:25.455 --> 05:27.501
-[chuckles]: You, too. Okay.
-Okay, I'll see you. All right.

05:29.807 --> 05:32.375
-Dad! Dad! Dad! Dad!
-Ah! Hey! Ah, there you are.
[babbles]

05:32.419 --> 05:34.246
-What do we got? What do we got?
-Can we go make s'mores

05:34.290 --> 05:36.553
-at the bonfire?
-Can we? Can we, please?

05:36.597 --> 05:39.643
Uh, this is a lot of sugar.
What'd your mom say?

05:39.687 --> 05:42.385
She said it's fine as long as
you get the stuff to make them.

05:42.429 --> 05:45.606
-As long as I get the stuff
to make them.
-If it's not too much trouble.

05:45.649 --> 05:47.259
No. No, I don't think it's
too much trouble. S'mores it is.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.609
-All right? Yeah?
-MADISON: [gasps] Yeah!
-[kids cheer]

05:48.652 --> 05:50.306
You get s'mores.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.221
Oh, we better get a jacket.

05:52.264 --> 05:53.004
-KEVIN: Yeah.
-MADISON: It's gonna be cold.

05:55.659 --> 05:57.400
Are you sure this isn't yours?

05:57.444 --> 05:59.533
[chuckles]:
No, this-this is not my luggage.

05:59.576 --> 06:02.013
Trust me, if this was my bag,
I would know.

06:02.057 --> 06:04.451
Well, if I were you, I might
just pretend it's mine to see

06:04.494 --> 06:05.843
what the heck
is inside this thing.

06:05.887 --> 06:08.977
-So, areyou sure?
-Yes.
-Ma'am?

06:09.020 --> 06:10.587
[chuckles]: Are you sure
that's not your bag?

06:10.631 --> 06:13.285
[chuckles]

06:13.329 --> 06:15.636
Uh, so, what-what happened?
The airport lose

06:15.679 --> 06:17.289
-your luggage?
-Yep.

06:17.333 --> 06:19.204
Now I'm totally screwed 'cause,

06:19.248 --> 06:20.684
you know, I just have

06:20.728 --> 06:22.817
this emergency pair of underwear
'cause you never want

06:22.860 --> 06:25.472
-to get stuck in an ER
with dirty drawers.
-Stuck at the ER.

06:25.515 --> 06:27.604
-That's your mom's number one...
-That's my mom's only... Yeah.

06:27.648 --> 06:29.867
...rule. Yeah.

06:33.523 --> 06:36.483
-[Sophie clears throat]
-Uh, okay, so, what do we do?
How do I fix this?

06:36.526 --> 06:38.572
-How do we get you clothes?
-Most of the stores in town

06:38.615 --> 06:39.660
close in half an hour.

06:39.703 --> 06:41.662
Things shut down early here.

06:41.705 --> 06:44.491
-You and Grant rent a car?
-Oh, no.

06:44.534 --> 06:46.884
No, he, uh, he actually
got stuck in New York.

06:46.928 --> 06:49.670
It's a long, boring story.

06:49.713 --> 06:51.672
-Just had to work.
-Um, I could drive you.

06:51.715 --> 06:53.848
-Oh, you don't have to.
-It's okay.

06:53.891 --> 06:54.936
I got to run into town
and grab some stuff anyway.

06:54.979 --> 06:56.459
I'll-I'll drive you.

06:56.503 --> 06:57.591
-Really? Are you sure?
-Yeah.

06:57.634 --> 07:00.115
Yeah. It's not a problem.

07:00.158 --> 07:02.247
-Okay.
-Okay. Can you
pull the car around?

07:02.291 --> 07:04.380
-Of course, right away.
-Yeah? All right, come on.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.164
[vehicle approaching]

07:15.391 --> 07:17.088
I rented it for Kate and Philip.

07:17.132 --> 07:18.481
So, it's either this

07:18.525 --> 07:20.048
-or a golf cart.
-[Sophie chuckles]

07:20.091 --> 07:21.397
SOPHIE:
Okay.

07:22.398 --> 07:23.355
Shall we?

07:24.618 --> 07:26.446
[car door opens]

07:32.539 --> 07:34.628
Uh...

07:34.671 --> 07:36.760
Just, uh... This is a lot,

07:36.804 --> 07:38.936
-right?
-Yeah, that's probably
a good call.

07:38.980 --> 07:40.416
-Yeah. Here you go.
-[car door closes]

07:40.460 --> 07:42.549
Okay. All right.

07:56.345 --> 07:57.999
[exhales]
Sorry, Soph.

07:58.042 --> 07:59.870
Looks like this was
our last option.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.524
SOPHIE:
Hmm.

08:05.180 --> 08:06.921
I think I have an idea.

08:15.930 --> 08:18.236
-Hi there.
-Hi.

08:18.280 --> 08:20.587
-SOPHIE: Hey.
-Just about to close.

08:20.630 --> 08:21.979
I'm sorry,
you don't happen to have

08:22.023 --> 08:24.199
a rack of unclaimed clothes,
do you?

08:24.242 --> 08:26.767
-[exhales]
-Look, I-I'm in town
for a wedding,

08:26.810 --> 08:29.552
and the airport lost my luggage.
[chuckles]

08:29.596 --> 08:31.249
I just...
I'm really in a bind here.

08:32.642 --> 08:34.296
[sighs]

08:36.777 --> 08:38.605
Watch your head.

08:38.648 --> 08:41.129
On the other side
with a red tag.

08:41.172 --> 08:42.565
Okay. Great. Thank you.

08:42.609 --> 08:44.959
-Uh, we'll be fast, I promise.
-Thank you.

08:46.613 --> 08:48.571
This is a little trick
my mom taught me

08:48.615 --> 08:50.617
after the divorce.

08:50.660 --> 08:52.619
Money was tight,
so we used to go thrifting.

08:52.662 --> 08:54.708
You never told me that.

08:54.751 --> 08:58.581
Um... Yeah, well,
it's not exactly something

08:58.625 --> 09:00.540
-that you go around
bragging about, you know.
-KEVIN: Mm.

09:03.194 --> 09:04.935
Come on, start looking.

09:04.979 --> 09:07.677
Oh. Yes, ma'am. Yes, ma'am.

09:14.466 --> 09:16.556
Um, how are...
how are your kids doing?

09:17.861 --> 09:20.647
Oh, uh, they're incredible.

09:20.690 --> 09:22.605
They're incredible.
And I know that's something

09:22.649 --> 09:25.652
that all parents say, you know,
that their kids are special.

09:25.695 --> 09:27.479
My kids are special.

09:27.523 --> 09:29.438
They really are, though.
They... They're special.

09:29.481 --> 09:31.701
And they're so different.
They're so different.

09:31.745 --> 09:34.051
Franny is this, um,
really precocious little girl.

09:34.095 --> 09:36.314
She's always asking questions.
She's very curious.

09:36.358 --> 09:39.796
And Nicky is this, uh...
a wild child

09:39.840 --> 09:41.668
who dives into things headfirst

09:41.711 --> 09:44.018
without even thinking.
Sometimes literally.

09:44.061 --> 09:46.890
-Hmm. Sounds familiar.
-Yes.

09:46.934 --> 09:49.806
-Karma. It's a five-year-old
running with scissors.
-[Sophie laughs]

09:52.504 --> 09:54.071
[exhales]

09:54.115 --> 09:55.638
Oh, this might work.

09:58.032 --> 10:00.643
Oh, yeah.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.471
And I think that we passed
a dressing room

10:02.514 --> 10:03.777
-right there. Yeah.
-Oh, great.

10:09.783 --> 10:12.655
Um, can you, uh, hold this up
'cause it's...?

10:12.699 --> 10:14.657
Oh, yeah, sure.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.877
-No problem.
-SOPHIE: Thank you.

10:16.920 --> 10:18.313
You got it.

10:21.751 --> 10:23.448
SOPHIE [chuckles]:
Oh, hey, I, uh...

10:23.492 --> 10:26.495
I recently saw a picture of you
in some magazine

10:26.538 --> 10:28.497
looking like one
of the Village People.

10:28.540 --> 10:31.108
Oh, yeah, that, um...
[chuckles]

10:31.152 --> 10:33.154
That was the GQprofile.

10:33.197 --> 10:34.677
I was trying to get press
for the nonprofit,

10:34.721 --> 10:36.331
and they insisted
that I wear a hard hat,

10:36.374 --> 10:39.377
so that's, uh, what that was.

10:39.421 --> 10:42.511
SOPHIE:
Oh. Well, it made me smile.

10:42.554 --> 10:44.600
At least it was
for a good cause.

10:44.644 --> 10:46.341
Okay,
you can let down the curtain.

10:46.384 --> 10:47.690
-KEVIN: Yeah?
-SOPHIE: Mm-hmm.

10:47.734 --> 10:48.778
-All right.
-[Sophie clears throat softly]

10:51.738 --> 10:53.696
[Sophie exhales]

10:55.916 --> 10:58.527
Yeah, this'll do.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.181
Yeah.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.662
I-I think
you'll get by just fine.

11:05.795 --> 11:07.318
So, yeah,
at first we weren't sure

11:07.362 --> 11:08.711
there'd be any interest,
but there's actually a...

11:08.755 --> 11:10.234
There's a big demand for it.

11:10.278 --> 11:12.106
These vets, they want...
they want connection, you know?

11:12.149 --> 11:13.629
They want community.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.979
Actually, this guy Hank,

11:16.023 --> 11:17.894
at a foundation pour last week,

11:17.938 --> 11:20.157
he tells me that working outside
with vets just like him

11:20.201 --> 11:21.768
gave him these little--
get this--

11:21.811 --> 11:24.596
pockets of peace.

11:24.640 --> 11:26.598
-Oh.
-Yeah. Peace that he said

11:26.642 --> 11:27.948
he didn't think
he'd ever be able to find.

11:27.991 --> 11:30.602
-Aw. Pockets of peace.
-Mm-hmm.

11:30.646 --> 11:33.170
-I love that.
-Me, too.

11:35.564 --> 11:37.392
So, how's saving lives
in the big city?

11:37.435 --> 11:39.089
-How's that going?
-Um, you know what?

11:39.133 --> 11:40.830
I'm actually saving lives

11:40.874 --> 11:43.528
outside a little town in Berlin
at the moment.

11:43.572 --> 11:46.140
Is that the-the German Berlin?

11:46.183 --> 11:48.359
Because I know there's, uh,
there's a Paris, Texas.

11:48.403 --> 11:51.928
-Uh, yeah, no. No,
it's the German one. [laughs]
-Okay.

11:51.972 --> 11:55.366
I'm-I'm working
as a traveling nurse now.

11:55.410 --> 11:58.021
-I didn't know that was a thing.
-Yeah. Yeah.

11:58.065 --> 12:00.763
Um, after my mom died,

12:00.807 --> 12:02.765
-I found this list
that she wrote.
-Uh-huh.

12:02.809 --> 12:06.813
Um, it was all these places
that she wanted to visit.

12:06.856 --> 12:08.858
So I made my own list.

12:08.902 --> 12:10.468
And we went

12:10.512 --> 12:13.341
-to Italy for our honeymoon.
-Mm-hmm.

12:13.384 --> 12:15.952
And then Paris.

12:15.996 --> 12:18.476
-You know, the French one.
-Wait, hold on a second.

12:18.520 --> 12:19.782
Did you say
that there's a French one?

12:19.826 --> 12:20.957
-There's a French one.
-Oh.

12:21.001 --> 12:22.872
-[chuckles]
-[imitates explosion]

12:22.916 --> 12:25.788
Yeah. And then my friend told me
about this traveling nurse gig,

12:25.832 --> 12:28.835
-so I just jumped
on the opportunity.
-Sounds like fun.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.619
It's got to be tough, though,
all that long distance

12:30.662 --> 12:31.663
with you and Grant, right?
I mean, that can't be...

12:31.707 --> 12:34.188
Oh, yeah, it is, but, um,

12:34.231 --> 12:37.408
you know, I can work
for a chunk and then,

12:37.452 --> 12:39.149
you know,
take a stretch off and...

12:39.193 --> 12:40.847
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

12:40.890 --> 12:44.198
I will admit, the, uh,
the red-eyes are killing me.

12:44.241 --> 12:46.896
-Yeah?
-Yeah. I'm getting old.

12:46.940 --> 12:49.856
-You're getting old?
I'm getting old.
-Oh, please.

12:49.899 --> 12:52.075
Kevin Pearson doesn't age.

12:52.119 --> 12:54.991
Kevin Pearson ages.
My beard's coming in gray.

12:55.035 --> 12:56.950
-No, it's not.
-It is, it is.
I'm thinking about dyeing it.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.690
-Right here on the corner.
Check it out. Look at...
-I don't believe you.

12:58.734 --> 12:59.953
-Get in there. Take a look.
-Let me see. Let me see.

12:59.996 --> 13:01.258
[gasps]
Oh, my God.

13:01.302 --> 13:03.695
-Yeah.
-You have gray hair.

13:03.739 --> 13:05.219
You are not allowed to dye that.

13:05.262 --> 13:06.220
I said I was thinking
about dyeing it.

13:06.263 --> 13:08.309
No, I forbid it.

13:17.579 --> 13:20.060
Last year, Nicky fell off
the jungle gym

13:20.103 --> 13:21.888
and cut his chin pretty bad.

13:21.931 --> 13:24.064
It was deep,

