33:06.245 --> 33:08.203
That doesn't mean
there aren't still

33:08.247 --> 33:11.467
summer vacations to be enjoyed.

33:11.511 --> 33:15.428
There's still love to be shared.

33:15.471 --> 33:18.735
It just all happens much faster.

33:18.779 --> 33:20.737
[singing inaudibly]

33:20.781 --> 33:22.522
♪

33:29.877 --> 33:31.922
[indistinct chatter]

33:31.966 --> 33:34.577
♪ Well, my friends,
the time has come♪

33:35.926 --> 33:38.451
♪ To raise the roof
and have some fun...♪

33:38.494 --> 33:40.975
-RANDALL: Yo.
-Hey.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.064
So, for real, bro.

33:43.108 --> 33:44.979
What happened with you
last night?

33:46.328 --> 33:48.287
Oh, last night--
It was a long story.

33:48.330 --> 33:50.941
-Is it a good story?
-Uh...

33:50.985 --> 33:52.421
I don't know yet.

33:52.465 --> 33:53.770
Um...

33:56.034 --> 33:58.253
Sophie's no longer married.

33:58.297 --> 34:00.255
She's a single woman.

34:00.299 --> 34:02.910
-Manny say what?
-BETH: I knew it.

34:02.953 --> 34:05.260
I knew it.
This cracks the case wide open.

34:05.304 --> 34:07.219
-[taps wall]
-I got to go find Madison.

34:09.699 --> 34:11.658
-♪ All night long♪
-♪ All night♪

34:11.701 --> 34:13.268
-♪ All night♪
-♪ All night♪

34:13.312 --> 34:15.314
-♪ All night long♪
-♪ All night♪

34:15.357 --> 34:17.011
Oh, Rebecca.

34:17.055 --> 34:19.013
♪ All night long...♪

34:19.057 --> 34:21.450
Your song was so beautiful.

34:21.494 --> 34:24.758
Thank you, sweetheart.

34:24.801 --> 34:27.152
Are you okay?

34:29.328 --> 34:31.286
[sighs]

34:31.330 --> 34:32.374
[tongue clicks]

34:38.293 --> 34:39.990
[sighs]

34:42.210 --> 34:43.994
It's Kevin, isn't it?

34:46.867 --> 34:50.349
I love my son,
but he is an idiot.

34:52.351 --> 34:55.267
-[both laugh]
-He is.

34:55.310 --> 34:59.314
I mean, he is 20 years old,
he's supposed to be, but...

35:02.100 --> 35:04.232
The timing is just off
right now.

35:06.016 --> 35:07.757
He isn't ready for you.

35:10.760 --> 35:12.980
He will be, but...

35:15.200 --> 35:18.594
...it's gonna take a while.

35:18.638 --> 35:23.338
And I don't know if you can
wait around for that.

35:23.382 --> 35:26.298
I mean, personally,
I don't know if I could.

35:26.341 --> 35:27.690
[exhales]

35:31.433 --> 35:33.914
But when the timing is right...

35:36.395 --> 35:38.223
...he's gonna be so great.

35:43.445 --> 35:44.925
Yeah.

35:48.711 --> 35:51.192
Wow, that's a lot, man.

35:51.236 --> 35:53.194
-Really is.
-Yeah.

35:53.238 --> 35:56.415
So, let me
get this straight. Um...

35:56.458 --> 35:59.679
the woman you've pined after
for years is finally single,

35:59.722 --> 36:01.681
and you're depressed about it?

36:03.291 --> 36:06.033
[exhales]
Just-- I don't want to...

36:06.076 --> 36:07.774
I don't want
to mess it up again.

36:07.817 --> 36:09.906
That's not gonna
happen, Captain.

36:09.950 --> 36:12.431
S-- Every time
we see each other,

36:12.474 --> 36:14.433
we blow up each other's
lives, it's-it's...

36:14.476 --> 36:16.435
I don't want
to do that, I don't...

36:16.478 --> 36:19.220
don't want to hurt her again.

36:19.264 --> 36:20.265
Huh.

36:23.050 --> 36:25.052
What are you doing?
What are you thinking?

36:25.095 --> 36:27.402
-I'm thinking about
the right thing to say here.
-Okay.

36:27.446 --> 36:28.882
I feel like you're at a moment
in life where you need

36:28.925 --> 36:31.014
really smart,
really sound advice.

36:31.058 --> 36:33.452
-Yes. Yes, please.
-Yeah. Okay. Yep.

36:33.495 --> 36:35.584
Okay, so this is...

36:35.628 --> 36:38.283
-This is what I got.
-Okay.

36:38.326 --> 36:40.285
Buffalo Bills
lost the Super Bowl

36:40.328 --> 36:42.504
four years in a row
when we were kids.

36:42.548 --> 36:44.289
-You remember that? Yeah.
-I do.

36:46.856 --> 36:48.945
-I'm not the Buffalo Bills.
-That's not what I'm saying.

36:48.989 --> 36:51.034
-Okay.
-Anyway, before
every Super Bowl,

36:51.078 --> 36:54.081
they make Super Bowl champion
merch with both teams on it

36:54.124 --> 36:56.431
so they have stuff ready
to go no matter who wins, right?

36:56.475 --> 36:58.825
-Mm-hmm.
-But once a team loses,

36:58.868 --> 37:01.610
they don't want the stuff
with the losing team on it.

37:01.654 --> 37:03.438
They don't want
"Super Bowl champion

37:03.482 --> 37:06.746
-Buffalo Bills" sweatshirts.
-Hmm.

37:06.789 --> 37:09.749
So, do you know
where that stuff used to go?

37:11.316 --> 37:12.317
I bet you're gonna tell me.

37:12.360 --> 37:13.622
-Other continents.
-Yeah?

37:13.666 --> 37:15.320
Africa. Asia.

37:15.363 --> 37:17.539
-Any and every nation in need.
-Huh.

37:17.583 --> 37:19.889
So, for four consecutive years
in the early '90s,

37:19.933 --> 37:22.327
there were world champion
Buffalo Bills merch

37:22.370 --> 37:24.851
flooding other continents.

37:24.894 --> 37:26.331
I-I don't know
where you're going...

37:26.374 --> 37:29.290
Kev, there are
tens of thousands of people

37:29.334 --> 37:30.770
who grew up thinking
that the Buffalo Bills

37:30.813 --> 37:34.513
were the greatest team
of all time.

37:34.556 --> 37:38.995
-The world
is friggin' insane, man.
-[laughs]

37:39.039 --> 37:42.172
It makes no sense.

37:42.216 --> 37:45.785
But you and Sophie together,

37:45.828 --> 37:49.484
now, that makes more sense
than most things.

37:49.528 --> 37:51.356
Hey.

37:51.399 --> 37:53.271
You're not gonna
screw it up this time.

37:54.359 --> 37:56.143
I know it.

38:00.626 --> 38:02.584
Thank you.

38:02.628 --> 38:04.369
♪

38:13.943 --> 38:16.381
-Hey.
-SOPHIE: Hi.

38:16.424 --> 38:17.469
-Talk to you?
-Yeah.

38:17.512 --> 38:19.384
-Yeah? Okay.
-Yes, sure.

38:19.427 --> 38:21.821
-Yes. Um...
-Uh...

38:21.864 --> 38:24.389
-Listen...
-I was actually gonna
come over and...

38:24.432 --> 38:27.043
I-I don't, I don't want you
to be a ball

38:27.087 --> 38:30.351
that I just bounce off of
to get to another ball.

38:30.395 --> 38:33.702
-What? Wait, just stop. I...
-I...

38:33.746 --> 38:36.401
Listen, y-you don't get
to give a speech this time.

38:36.444 --> 38:37.967
Okay? It-It's my turn.

38:39.752 --> 38:40.796
Okay.

38:43.408 --> 38:47.629
Look, I-I have spent
years of my life

38:47.673 --> 38:50.415
praying that you would...
[laughs] you would grow up.

38:54.244 --> 38:55.681
But...

38:57.030 --> 39:00.860
Now here you are,
20 years later...

39:03.079 --> 39:05.081
...and you're finally the man
that I always knew

39:05.125 --> 39:06.431
you possibly could be.

39:06.474 --> 39:09.651
♪ How did it feel to be alone?♪

39:09.695 --> 39:12.393
At first, I-- honestly,
I didn't believe it,

39:12.437 --> 39:15.744
that we could finally be in the
right place at the right time.

39:15.788 --> 39:18.268
♪ I was always thinking
of games...♪

39:18.312 --> 39:20.009
You know?

39:20.053 --> 39:24.231
And that I would finally be
the best version of myself.

39:24.274 --> 39:26.494
♪ The best of my time...♪

39:26.538 --> 39:29.279
But I am.

39:29.323 --> 39:30.803
And you are.

39:32.587 --> 39:36.591
And... I don't know,
I freaked out.

39:36.635 --> 39:38.288
I freaked out last night
because I just don't,

39:38.332 --> 39:40.421
I don't want us to fall back

39:40.465 --> 39:44.425
into the old versions
of ourselves.

39:44.469 --> 39:47.515
-You know?
-Mm.

39:47.559 --> 39:52.041
I need you to love me
for the woman that I am now,

39:52.085 --> 39:53.695
not the woman that I was.

39:56.132 --> 39:58.265
'Cause you're not the man
that you were.

40:00.876 --> 40:03.531
And I want to fall in love
with the man that you've become.

40:03.575 --> 40:07.274
♪ I have a friend I've...♪

40:07.317 --> 40:08.928
That was a ram--
that was a ramble.

40:08.971 --> 40:11.887
-I rambled.
-No.

40:11.931 --> 40:13.323
What were you gonna say?

40:17.545 --> 40:21.941
Well, I-I think in lieu of
you not wanting to repeat

40:21.984 --> 40:23.725
the patterns of the past,
I think it's-it's better if I...

40:23.769 --> 40:26.293
No, just say it.

40:26.336 --> 40:27.903
-Okay, again, I think,
in lieu of you...
-Stop saying

40:27.947 --> 40:29.949
"in lieu of," you're not even
using the word correctly.

40:29.992 --> 40:31.907
-Really?
-Yeah.

40:31.951 --> 40:34.475
[laughs]:
Wha-What were you gonna say?

40:34.519 --> 40:37.478
♪ Love can break your heart♪

40:37.522 --> 40:39.088
[exhales]

40:39.132 --> 40:42.744
♪ Try to be sure♪

40:42.788 --> 40:47.096
♪ Right from the start♪

40:47.140 --> 40:50.099
♪ Yes, only love♪

40:50.143 --> 40:54.539
♪ Can break your heart...♪

